Modit.js

Modit is a Javascript module library designed for testability. It encourages highly testable, decoupled, encapsulated designed.

== Installation ==

# Install node.js
wget http://nodejs.org/dist/node-v0.1.103.tar.gz
tar -xf node-v0.1.103.tar.gz
cd node-v0.1.103
./configure
make
sudo make install

== Using Modit ==

Creating javascript modules with modit saves you a lot of boilerplate code. Compare this:

to this:

But the real power of modit comes in it's mocking library. Modit makes it very easy to mock out dependencies between modules.

== Running Tests == 

$ gem install watchr
$ watchr nodejs.watchr
